Author: jamesbritt
Content:
This is a good tutorial. It's the first I found that showed how to do some basic but useful stuff, such as compile, include external files, and have code write to STDOUT. The other Haskell articles I'd seen jumped right into type theory and such; I prefer hands-on.

With Scheme in 48 Hours you get running code you can hack around with to see what does what.
